Answer: The NullPointerException is thrown because the system is trying to find a view with the id R.id.tv_scoreDisplay before the activity's layout has been set. The setContentView(R.layout.activity_five_zero_one) method must be called before findViewById(R.id.tv_scoreDisplay).

A: You are getting a NullPointerException because you are trying to find a view before the activity's layout has been set.
You should call setContentView(R.layout.activity_five_zero_one) before findViewById(R.id.tv_scoreDisplay).
Here is an example:
public class FiveZeroOne extends AppCompatActivity {

    private TextView tv_scoreDisplay;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_five_zero_one);

        tv_scoreDisplay = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.tv_scoreDisplay);
    }

    public void someMethod() {
        tv_scoreDisplay.setText("Some text");
    }

    public void someOtherMethod() {
        tv_scoreDisplay.setText("Some other text");
    }
}

In this example, setContentView(R.layout.activity_five_zero_one) is called in the onCreate() method, and findViewById(R.id.tv_scoreDisplay) is called in the onCreate() method and in the two methods someMethod() and someOtherMethod(). This way, the TextView is only initialized once, and you can use it in multiple methods.

